cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

This paper deals with object detection and pose estimation, which are core topics in computer vision (cs.CV). It also addresses the problem of next-best-view prediction, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of unsupervised feature learning and clustering techniques also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the evaluation of the proposed framework on challenging datasets indicates a potential interest in graphics (cs.GR) as well.
